SFLphone is an open-source SIP/IAX2 compatible enterprise-class softphone, published under the GNU Public License 3.

CLI client and daemon are build by default.
Video support can be added with WITH_VIDEO=yes option. This requires ffmpeg.
Pulseaudio support can be added with WITH_PULSE=yes option. This requires pulseaudio.
To build the KDE client use BUILD_KDE=yes. (WITH_VIDEO disabled temporarily... WIP).
To build the GTK client use BUILD_GTK=yes. This requires cogl, clutter, clutter-gtk.

NOTE: This SlackBuild is a work in progress and not every thing works properly yet.
      Use in a production or critical environment is not encouraged or recommended at this time.
